  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study aims to evaluate the possible Correlation Between Serum Levels of Markers of
      Neuronal Injury and Cognitive Dysfunction after Coronary Artery Bypass Surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The systemic inflammatory response after cardiac surgery may cause damage to the central
      nervous system and elevated markers of brain injury in peripheral blood. This event may be
      potentially related to the development of postoperative cognitive dysfunction (POCD), with
      incidences varying from 20 to 83%.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
